assetDescriptions.description:
Description

Anderson Munger YMCA run club is a running club that is starting from ground zero. We will be focusing on training our runner on proper running techniques, cardio vascular endurance, and building community within our group. The ultimate goal that will come with our training will be to complete in a 5k, 10k, half, and a full marathon.

Activity

SGT Angerson Munger Run Club #221494

Sub-Activities

  • SGT Angerson Munger Run Club- February
  • SGT Angerson Munger Run Club- January

assetDescriptions.description:
**Registration is OPEN now at www.FinishTheRide.org/ftr-griffith-park**

 

#NEVERGIVEUP!

 

Join hundreds of cyclists, runners, walkers and many others to enjoy the beautiful scenery and back roads of Griffith Park. Our rides take you on a journey through the park and surrounding areas and our runs/walks travel around the most tranquil areas of Griffith Park. Top it all off at our wonderful end event venue.

 

The event benefits:

Streets Are For Everyone (SAFE) -- a non-profit organization whose mission is to improve the quality of life for pedestrians, bicyclists and drivers alike by working to reduce traffic caused fatalies to Zero. 

SAFE addresses this problem in a holistic fashion through direct education, broad awareness campaigns, partnerships, community outreach, policy and legislation, support for those impacted and other proven strategies.

 

Check out FinishTheRide.org for videos and information on the origin of Finish The Ride.

 

The event includes:

 

Run = 5K, 10K and Half Marathon

Walk = 5K, 10K

  • Free t-shirt OR socks with registration
  • Chip timing (5K, 10K and Half Marathon only) and NEW individual event medals awarded for ALL events!
  • Live music and dancing!
  • Free festival and safety expo with giveaways, raffles, prizes and activities for the kids. Food will also be available. END EVENT EXPO ENDS PROMPTLY AT 1PM. Feel free to bring the whole family, even the dog!

Join Finish The Run Griffith Park 2020 not only for yourself, but for those who survived, those who didn't and the safety of ALL on our streets!

 

#FinishTheRide #FinishTheRun #NeverGiveUp

For more information on the event itself and how you can help, e-mail us at Register@FinishTheRide.org or call (844) 884-7233 Ext. 801.

 

Event details and schedule

When: Sunday, September 20, 2020

Where: Crystal Springs Area, Griffith Park

4669 Crystal Springs Drive

Los Angeles, CA 90027

 

Registration/Check-in opens at 6am, it is recommended that you arrive at least 30 minutes before your event start to register and 15 minutes before your event start if you are already pre-registered to pick up your bib.

Schedule (exact event start times are subject to change):

  • 6:00 AM Check-in/Registration opens
  • 8:00 AM Opening Ceremony/Special Speakers
  • 8:15 AM Half Marathon Start
  • 9:00 AM 5K/10K Run/Walk Start

EXPO ENDS AT 1PM

Post event festivities include live music, food, drink, free stuff from sponsors, activities for the kids and a raffle!

assetDescriptions.description:
It's time for the Father's Day 5k, 10k, 15k, Half Marathon!! 

New safer modified format!

Small ~10 person or less waves

WAVE 1 7:30AM Half Marathon

WAVE 2 7:40AM 15k & 10k

WAVE 4 7:45AM 5k

WAVE 5 7:50AM 5k

- early start, self time, or later start self time options are also available - please email abetterworldrunning@yahoo.com

Date - Sunday, June 21st, 2020

Address -  2000 Ocean Ave. Santa Monica, CA

Off of beach path off of Bay St. & Ocean Ave. near Crescent Bay Park

Event details and schedule

Start - 7:30AM - 9:30AM, finish by 10:30AM, or finish on your own time and email us the time

​

New safer modified format to run your own race and stay safe:

- opportunity to run your own race and pick up your medal and goodie bag and have results posted online that day

- staggered start times (must sign up for start time, can do it through active.com or email us your preferred start time abetterworldrunning@yahoo.com, or you can start on your own)

- no gathering before, during or after

- no group running/walking unless with a member of your household

- practice social/physical distancing at all times, keeping at least 6 feet apart from others at all times

- no touch points, no aid station

- please bring personal face covering to have on hand at all times

- bring your own water/sports drink, nutrition, can use your own car to refill on your sports nutrition

- qualifies for Half Fanatics "pop up race"

- use an app or watch to track your time/distance and email or message us your time

- course will be marked

- new waiver found on pdf icon below must be signed beforehand electronically through active.com, or sent via email, new waiver updated as of 6/14

https://www.abetterworldrunning.com/waiver

- if not feeling well, exhibiting symptoms of illness please stay home

- stay safe and race solo

​

- option to transfer to a later date or have your medal mailed will be completed upon emailing us at abetterworldrunning@yahoo.com

​

 

Start - 7:30AM - 9:30AM

New safer modified format!

Small ~10 person or less waves

WAVE 1 7:30AM Half Marathon

WAVE 2 7:40AM 15k & 10k

WAVE 4 7:45AM 5k

WAVE 5 7:50AM 5k

- early start, self time, or later start self time options are also available - please email abetterworldrunning@yahoo.com

​

CHECK IN:

7:00AM-7:30AM 

* additional option to start earlier, or on your own time and keep track of your time and distance with an app or gps watch

 

Course map: The course is super easy to follow.  It will consist of counter clockwise loops around the beach path that will be marked.

5k (1 loop), 10k (2 loops), 15k (3 loops):

http://www.gmap-pedometer.com/?r=6245011

 

Half marathon is 3 x 4.36 mile loops:

http://www.gmap-pedometer.com/?r=6245013

​

 

NO REFUNDS.

 

Date - Sunday, June 21st, 2020

 

Address -  2000 Ocean Ave. Santa Monica, CA

Off of beach path off of Bay St. & Ocean Ave. near Crescent Bay Park

 

Parking -  Meters on the street are free until 9AM. After 9AM, you are responsible to pay for the parking meter with quarters, or credit cards.  ** On Saturday there is street sweeping from 7-9AM.  Please check the signs on the meters to indicate where there is no parking on Saturday from 7-9AM.  The beach parking lot has an all day flat fee that can be paid through machine, or when the booth is open.  The price varies from $8-10 depending on the season.

assetDescriptions.description:
About Jeff Galloway’s Program:

The Galloway Run/Walk/Run Training Program is open to anyone who is interested in fulfilling a lifetime goal: of running a 5k, half marathon, or marathon. The training group welcomes all levels, from beginners to Boston qualifiers.  Pace groups are set up to ensure a comfortable and safe training pace for every ability.  We would love to have you but, if you're not certain about whether to join, email us at LongBeachGalloway@gmail.com. 

Event details and schedule

General Info:

Contact Program Director Kelley Tenny at LongBeachGalloway@gmail.com or 714-235-2112. We are excited to have you Run/Walk/Run with us!

Is this group right for me?

The Jeff Galloway training approach is suitable for all levels and all ages! We focus on achieving your goal distance, injury free while having fun and building fitness. Bring a friend and join us for one of our Saturday morning weekly group runs (first session is free) and experience great camaraderie, effective training and lots of support. Email us for more information.

https://www.facebook.com/LBGalloway/

 

Programs:

  • 5K Training 
  • Half Marathon Training

Kick Off

6/20/2020 at 7:00am

El Dorado Park

2800 Studebaker Ave

Long Beach, CA 90808

 

 

Join us to train for the following events this year.

Long Beach Half Marathon, Long Beach 5K, Surf City Half Marathon & 5K, OC Half Marathon & 5K 

Training Program membership does not include race entry fees.

 

 Refund Policy:

The training fee is non-refundable. Requests for refunds are considered for medical reasons only, must be accompanied by a physician’s letter and must be submitted prior to the half-way point in the training season. A $25 processing fee will be retained. People who want to try out Galloway Training may attend up to two group runs free of charge before registering for the season.

assetDescriptions.description:
Known as "The Friendliest Race in L.A.", the Valley Crest Half Marathon is a popular trail half-marathon on historic Mulholland fire road that treats runners to beautiful spring foliage and magnificent valley and ocean views. In it's 19th year, this challenging but fast race makes perfect competition for the serious runner and is also "user friendly" enough to be a great first-timer trail run! The course is entirely on city-maintained fire roads in early June and typically has cool, overcast weather. We look forward to having you run with us!

Event details and schedule

VALLEY CREST HALF MARATHON RACE FEATURES

  • Half Marathon @ 7:30 a.m.
  • 10K Trail Run @ 7:45 a.m.
  • Men's and Ladies' Technical Blend Race Shirts
  • Customized Finisher Medals
  • Awards to First Place Overall Male & Female 
  • ​Awards to First Place Male & Female finishers in five-year Age Divisions
  • Water stations at mile 2.5, 4.5, 7, 10 - all runners should carry one bottle 
  • Approximately 1700' of elevation gain and loss
  • 4 hours to complete the course
  • Computerized Chip Timing
  • Race Day Registration and Bib Pick Up will begin at 6:00 a.m.

If a person does not complete a half marathon or any other distance, then we WILL make a distance that the person completed in increments of common standard distances: 5k, 10k, 10mi, half marathon, marathon, etc. ALL finishers get a medal. FYI Also to save money, you can just mail the fee along with all your info, email: abetterworldrunning@yahoo.com for more info.

ENTRY FORMS CAN BE FOUND ON OUR WEBSITE www.abetterworldrunning.com. All results will be posted after the event on our website usually the evening of the event.

Everyone will get a medal as well as a goodie bag. Results are posted after every race on www.abetterworldrunning.com

Free photos are posted on our facebook page -- www.facebook.com/abetterworldrunning

We emphasize a more relaxed, fun and personal racing experience!

OFFICIAL TIMES AND PLACES WILL BE POSTED ON OUR WEBSITE: www.abetterworldrunning.com

NO REFUNDS NO BANDITS

assetDescriptions.description:
Welcome to a new era of women's running!

Come join StartLine Racing for their 2nd annual Women's Run Series.

This event will feature a Half Marathon, 10K, 5K and Butterfly Dash at Shoreline Aquatic Park.

All participants will receive their choice of a tech hoodie, tech short sleeve shirt or tech racerback tank.  Butterfly Dash participants will receive a short sleeve tech shirt with their registration.

Tons of water stations and restrooms!

So bring your family and your friends and spend the morning running with StartLine Racing!

 

About The Women's Run Series

Making Your Run Meaningful and Welcoming.

Everyone deserves a positive and supportive running environment. The Women's Run Series eliminates any feeling of intimidation or inadequacy that many race environments create. Instead, we offer a supportive space, that when you leave you will feel empowered and accomplished. It's a safe place to run, or walk, that isn't about winning, it's about coming together as women to finish and celebrate.

Your wings already exist.  All you have to do is FLY!

 

Butterfly Dash Information 

This event is for our younger participants and for those who want to run with mom!  It is an untimed run and is approximately a half mile in distance.  A parent wishing to run with their child does not need to register in order to do so. 

All Butterfly Dash participants will receive the following:

  • Custom Dri Fit Short Sleeve Event Shirt
  • Custom Finisher's Medal
  • Custom Event Bib
  • Drawstring Bag

 

Charity Partner

 

We are proud to be partnered with Girls on the Run of Los Angeles County for this event!  

 

Girls on the Run is a transformational physical activity based positive youth development program for girls in 3rd-8th grade. They teach life skills through dynamic interactive lessons and running games. The program culminates with the girls being physically and emotionally prepared to complete a celebratory 5k running event. The goal of the program is to unleash confidence through accomplishment while establishing a lifetime appreciation of health and fitness. 

 

At Girls on the Run they envision a world where all girls know and activate their limitless potential.  And more than that, they are working to make that vision a reality - one where girls can navigate their lives with confidence and joy.  One girl at a time, they've changed a million lives.  With your support, one girl at a time, they will change a million more.

Event details and schedule

Half Marathon Course Map

10K Course Map

5K Course Map

 

 

Mail-in Registration Form

To register by mail please complete and return our Mail-in Registration Form!  Please make checks payable to StartLine Racing.

 

 

Virtual Details

 

Of course we want you to participate in the Half Marathon, 10k, and 5k locally but we know things come up. So, if you can't join us on race day and still want to run, get the medal and swag you still can! Here is your way to take part in this epic event no matter where you are! And of course, all prices include shipping! Please note that your packet will be mailed to you after the completion of the event on September 6th.

Virtual Registrations are restricted to US addresses only.  If you reside outside of the US and wish to participate please contact StartLine Racing at info@startlineracing.com

 

 

All Participants Receive:

- Custom Event Finisher's Medal.  

- Custom event bib

- Drawstring Bag

- Choice of Custom Event Dri-Fit Tech long sleeve hoodie, Dri-Fit Tech short sleeve shirt or a Dri-Fit Tech Racer back Tank for all participants. 

- Age Group Awards for Top Three in all Female Age Groups (Race day participants only) (Men are not eligible for awards).  Our age groups are the following:

  • 8 & Under, 9 & 10, 11-13, 14-17, 18-24, 25-29, 30-34, 35-39, 40-44, 45-49, 50-54, 55-59, 60-64, 65-69, 70-74, 75 & Over

- Pre- and Post-Race "Runner's Brunch" (granola bars, fruit, water, Gatorade, etc) 

- Real Time Results and Photos on our Website or Mobile App (on Apple and Google) 

 

 

Race Day Information

  • Race Day Registration will be available beginning at 6am at Shoreline Aquatic Park.

    • We accept cash, check, and credit cards on race day 

    • PLEASE NOTE - Your swag selection and size are not guaranteed for those who register on race day.

  • Race day registration fees will be:

    • Half Marathon - $90

    • 10K - $70

    • 5K - $50

    • Butterfly Dash - $25

  • Please no pets allowed

  • We welcome wheelchairs, strollers & wagons.

  • No roller blades, skateboards or motorized devices are allowed on the run or walk courses.

  • The half marathon course has a 4 hour time limit.

  • Due to the common start/finish line, there is no bag check for this event.

 

 

Course Information

 

Aid/Water Stations

 

Water and Gatorade will be located at the following locations:

  • Half Marathon: Miles .75, 1.7, 2.85, 3.75, 4.9, 5.85 (turnaround), 6.85, 8, 8.87, 10, 11, and 12.4
  • 10K: Miles .75, 1.7, 2.85, 3.75 (turnaround), 4.71, and 5.48
  • 5K: Mile .75, 1.55 (turnaround), and 2.35
GU Gels will be available for half marathon runners at miles 4.9 and 6.85.

Restrooms will be located at the following locations:
  • Half Marathon: Miles 1.7, 2.85, 4, 5.5, 6.25, 7.75, 9, 10, and 11.5
  • 10K: Miles 1.7, 2.85, and 4.71
  • 5K: Mile 1.55 (turnaround)

 

 

Packet Pick-up Opportunities

 

Packet pick-up will be available on Saturday, September 5th from 2-5pm at Runner's High (map)

Race day packet pick-up available at Shoreline Aquatic Park (race location) starting at 6:00am.
